{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OrangeThemeTextInputComponentTokensProvider","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Define your own provider for input text component tokens","    \/\/ by inheriting from existing provider","    class CustomTextInputComponentTokensProvider: OrangeThemeTextInputComponentTokensProvider {","","        \/\/ Then override the text input component tokens you want.","","        override var sizeMaxWidth: SizeSemanticToken { DimensionRawTokens._3000 }","","        override var spacePaddingBlockDefault: SpaceSemanticToken { spaces.paddingInlineSmall }","","        override var colorBorderEnabled: MultipleColorSemanticTokens { colors.repositoryOpacityBlackHigher }","","        override var borderWidthDefault: BorderWidthSemanticToken { borders.widthMedium}","","        \/\/ ...","    }","","    \/\/ Or define your own provider from scratch","    class CustomTextInputComponentTokensProvider: TextInputComponentTokens {","","        \/\/ And implement hunders of tokens.","        \/\/ You are allowed to give semantic tokens providers if you want to define values.","    }"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Then, you can give this ","type":"text"},{"code":"CustomTextInputComponentTokensProvider","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to your own theme implementation:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["class LocalTheme: OrangeTheme {","","    override init() {","        super.init(textInput: CustomTextInputComponentTokensProvider())","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"or to an already existing theme for example:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    O